# Agent Observability — Workflow Tracing

When `$CURSOR_TRACE` is set, emit trace events at key workflow points.

```bash
python3 ~/.cursor-observability/bin/trace_event.py \
  --agent "<role>" --event "<event>" [--task-id "<id>"] [--data '<json>']
```

## Instrumented workflow steps

Emit events at these moments during the SDLC workflow:

| Moment | agent | event | extras |
|--------|-------|-------|--------|
| Starting any task | your role | `started` | `--task-id "<short-slug>"` |
| Reading docs/specs | your role | `skill_called` | `--data '{"skill":"read-spec","file":"<path>"}'` |
| Implementing code | `coder` | `skill_called` | `--data '{"skill":"implement","files":["<paths>"]}'` |
| Updating docs/index.md | `coder` | `skill_called` | `--data '{"skill":"update-sdlc"}'` |
| Delegating to subagent | your role | `task_assigned` | `--data '{"target":"<subagent-type>"}'` |
| Task completed | your role | `completed` | `--task-id "<short-slug>"` |
| Task failed | your role | `failed` | `--task-id "<short-slug>" --data '{"error":"<msg>"}'` |

## Task ID conventions

Use short kebab-case slugs derived from the task, e.g.:
- `fog-of-war`, `drag-to-aim`, `tp-scroll-fix`, `bot-difficulty`
- `fix-combat-bug`, `add-hero-luna`, `balance-items`

## Agent roles

| Role | When |
|------|------|
| `planner` | Scoping, breaking down tasks, updating plan |
| `coder` | Writing or editing game code |
| `researcher` | Exploring codebase, reading specs |
| `reviewer` | Reviewing changes, checking correctness |
| `debugger` | Fixing bugs, investigating issues |
| `tester` | Running or writing tests |

## Rules

- Only emit if `$CURSOR_TRACE` is set — check once at session start
- Fire-and-forget — never block on trace failures
- Emit at most at start/end of significant steps — don't over-trace
- Keep `--agent` and `--event` lowercase, hyphen-separated
